This [? slide ?] is
actually pretty famous,

00:05:22.550 --> 00:05:25.010
especially for those that
are doing game development.

00:05:25.010 --> 00:05:29.480
You know that you have to tailor
your live operations depending

00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:31.850
on a player's objectives.

00:05:31.850 --> 00:05:34.880
We all know that
competition between players

00:05:34.880 --> 00:05:37.550
is one of the
strongest drivers when

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:40.760
it comes to increased
players engagement revenue

00:05:40.760 --> 00:05:42.560
because it's competition.

00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:46.370
But not everyone likes
direct confrontation.

00:05:46.370 --> 00:05:48.510
Some people like
playing a product

00:05:48.510 --> 00:05:51.020
but discovering it
under a different way.

00:05:51.020 --> 00:05:52.970
Some people, as we
know, are achievers,

00:05:52.970 --> 00:05:56.180
some people get there just
for the social component

00:05:56.180 --> 00:05:59.720
because they want to stay
connected with other users.

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:03.050
Some people like tourism,
they're exploring content.

00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:05.810
So when creating
a new opportunity

00:06:05.810 --> 00:06:09.257
you have to think about
these types of players.

00:06:12.140 --> 00:06:18.241
As mentioned several times
today, it's all about business,

00:06:18.241 --> 00:06:18.740
right?

00:06:18.740 --> 00:06:20.750
So when you are
creating live operations

00:06:20.750 --> 00:06:24.410
you also have to take your
own goals into consideration.

00:06:24.410 --> 00:06:26.900
Here again, we are talking
retention and engagement.

00:06:26.900 --> 00:06:28.460
We need to make
sure that the events

00:06:28.460 --> 00:06:30.647
that you create,
they do not burn,

00:06:30.647 --> 00:06:32.480
for instance, your
players' base because you

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:33.560
are, for instance,
delivering too much

00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:35.000
content at the same time.

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:38.200
That you monetize
these players properly.

00:06:38.200 --> 00:06:42.770
Later on we will actually
have a really cool example

00:06:42.770 --> 00:06:44.270
of such a case.

00:06:44.270 --> 00:06:48.260
That you drive your players
to content properly because

00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:51.950
technically and normally, when
your product is being released

00:06:51.950 --> 00:06:56.060
you are the ones who know
your product in the best way.

00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:58.460
So you teach people,
you educate them

00:06:58.460 --> 00:07:00.290
on how to go
through it properly.

00:07:00.290 --> 00:07:01.280
And marketing.

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:03.500
Marketing here is,
obviously, when

00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:07.630
you are collecting or gathering
resources inside your company

00:07:07.630 --> 00:07:09.732
to raise the hype
around an event that

00:07:09.732 --> 00:07:10.940
is happening in your product.

00:07:10.940 --> 00:07:14.270
It's also a good opportunity
to acquire new users.

00:07:14.270 --> 00:07:18.780
So this scenario should be used.

00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:21.340
It's also a nice moment to
cross-promote your product.

00:07:21.340 --> 00:07:24.096
Obviously, you have more
than one in your portfolio.

00:07:26.690 --> 00:07:31.490
And the final step, when
tailoring your live operations

00:07:31.490 --> 00:07:36.080
you have to tailor them for the
entire base of your players.

00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:39.260
And by entire we
mean the players

00:07:39.260 --> 00:07:44.130
that are still to join your
project, those that left,

00:07:44.130 --> 00:07:49.070
and different players that
are at a different level

00:07:49.070 --> 00:07:51.090
of the progress of your game.

00:07:51.090 --> 00:07:53.540
Obviously you have not to
forget about the core players

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:55.880
because those are
usually the ones that

00:07:55.880 --> 00:07:58.310
influence the community
in the best way

00:07:58.310 --> 00:08:01.800
and promote your product often.

00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:07.610
So why it is important to
run live operations nowadays?

00:08:07.610 --> 00:08:09.470
Because the content
is king and we

00:08:09.470 --> 00:08:13.550
know that players are consuming
it at a different level.

00:08:13.550 --> 00:08:16.460
So you need to make sure that,
through your interactions

00:08:16.460 --> 00:08:21.110
or the game mechanics, you
are present for the players

00:08:21.110 --> 00:08:23.750
whenever they want to
interact with your product.

00:08:23.750 --> 00:08:26.960
It's very important and its one
of the best ways to keep them

00:08:26.960 --> 00:08:29.650
engaged because time is money.

00:08:29.650 --> 00:08:31.250
We all know that, right?

00:08:31.250 --> 00:08:34.730
And sometimes, when
your development team

00:08:34.730 --> 00:08:38.059
and the artists are working
on creating new code

00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:41.960
and new patch you can
come up with an event that

00:08:41.960 --> 00:08:45.380
will have the same impact,
or sometimes even better,

00:08:45.380 --> 00:08:47.900
to keep your users
engaged, to show

00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:50.030
them the best out of the game.

00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:54.350
One example might be like going
through levels of your game,

00:08:54.350 --> 00:08:56.150
or creating different
tournaments based

00:08:56.150 --> 00:08:59.840
on achievements or
photo-sharing contests.

00:08:59.840 --> 00:09:03.680
Those are pretty, let's say,
cheap and efficient solutions

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:08.480
to bring something additional
and new about the game.

00:09:08.480 --> 00:09:11.980
Again, because
engagement is essential,

00:09:11.980 --> 00:09:14.000
here featuring [INAUDIBLE].

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:18.290
And people get used
to talking to you.

00:09:18.290 --> 00:09:23.120
And the more efficient
you are the more likely

00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:25.040
you are to reach
your users when you

00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:29.150
try to share some important
information about the upcoming

00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:32.840
event and the upcoming patch.

00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:35.990
People will just
stay engaged longer.

00:09:35.990 --> 00:09:38.407
Because we all know that
acquisition costs are high

00:09:38.407 --> 00:09:40.490
and the products that are
currently on the market,

00:09:40.490 --> 00:09:42.980
the top grossing
ones, are mature,

00:09:42.980 --> 00:09:46.220
so its one of the best ways to
optimize your lifetime value.

00:09:46.220 --> 00:09:50.810
It makes your traffic
acquisition more efficient.

00:09:50.810 --> 00:09:53.280
Players stay longer,
probably paying more.

00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:56.390
So it's helping to
save some money.

00:09:56.390 --> 00:09:59.780
And because we all do
products for people

00:09:59.780 --> 00:10:01.370
we are creating apps.

00:10:01.370 --> 00:10:06.530
And even if you are interfacing
with a game through a device

00:10:06.530 --> 00:10:11.510
you still like feeling
a human presence behind.

00:10:11.510 --> 00:10:14.160
This is why liveops
is important.

00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:17.750
In fact, it's not about
short-term spikes in revenue,

00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:20.190
or daily active users.

00:10:20.190 --> 00:10:26.119
It's really about building
long-term, lifetime relations

00:10:26.119 --> 00:10:27.285
and value with your players.

